was at 2800 cfs. Totally bigger waves than i expected but it was a ton of fun!! Definitely not all<br/>
class II runs at these leves. The last rapid had some pretty huge waves at these levels and my<br/>
friend almost lost his kayak in this section. As of saturday i did not see any strainers in the<br/>
main channel of the creek...just fun fast water. </div>
